## Section 0 — Time Sourced Definition

"Time Sourced" means: distributed under this license, at cost, with attribution, with no exclusive control over access.

This work and all derivatives are Time Sourced. Derivatives must remain Time Sourced. The chain does not break.

---

## Section 1 — Time Sourced Requirement

Any derivative work, modification, compilation, integration, translation, or reformulation of this work must be distributed under this license or a license equally permissive. Derivatives may not impose additional restrictions. The Time Sourced chain is permanent and non-waivable by any party including the original author.

---

## Section 2 — Cost Minimization

Maximum allowable markup over verified cost-of-goods and labor: 5%. "Verified cost" means publicly auditable cost with no hidden padding. The following do not qualify as verified cost:

- Patent-period pricing surcharges (charging above cost during exclusivity periods)
- Pay-for-delay surcharges (costs imposed due to reverse payment settlements)
- Formulary exclusion fees (payments to restrict competing access)
- REMS (Risk Evaluation and Mitigation Strategy) abuse surcharges
- Data exclusivity recoupment
- Evergreening extension costs

Any pricing structure that embeds any of the above is not Time Sourced and trips the Human Rights Bar in Section 5.

---

## Section 3 — Non-Exclusivity

No entity may acquire exclusive rights to this work or any derivative. Non-exclusivity is permanent. It cannot be waived, transferred, contracted away, or overridden by any agreement, regulatory approval, or court order. No license in this work grants exclusivity. No sublicense may purport to grant exclusivity.

---

## Section 4 — Downstream Permanence

Every entity that receives this work, in any form, in any jurisdiction, receives it under these terms. The chain applies to: individuals, corporations, nonprofits, government entities, academic institutions, and any other legal or quasi-legal entity. The chain does not weaken downstream.

