## Section 11 — Author Defensive Provisions

(a) **Prior Art Preservation**: This work, its publication date, the accompanying `narrative.md`, `README.md`, `PROVENANCE.md`, and `venturi_no_mixer.scad` constitute prior art against any patent claim covering: the therapeutic use of these 42 molecules in neonatal populations, the synthesis routes described, the intervention mappings, the deployment logic, and the venturi iNO delivery device design. Any patent filed after the publication date of this work that purports to claim novelty over content described herein is invalid on its face.

(b) **Sole Authorship**: This work was independently created by Tyler "The TimeLord" Roost. No employer, contractor, institution, or collaborative partner has any ownership claim. This work was not created within the scope of employment. No work-for-hire doctrine applies.

(c) **Employment and NDA Non-Applicability**: No employment agreement, NDA, IP assignment clause, contractor agreement, or similar instrument entered into by the author at any point in time applies to this work. This work was created independently, using independent resources, in the author's own time, on problems not within any employer's line of business.

(d) **Anti-Discovery Abuse**: Any discovery process in litigation against the author that seeks documents, communications, or records relating to this work is limited to materials directly relevant to the specific legal claim. Fishing expeditions designed to identify other independent research, personal communications, or financial information unrelated to the specific claim are not permissible and will be opposed.

(e) **Bad-Faith Litigation Costs**: Any entity that brings a legal action against the author arising from this work and does not prevail on the primary claim owes the author: actual legal costs, $500,000 minimum, or 10% of the entity's annual revenue — whichever is greatest. "Bad faith" is established by bringing claims without reasonable likelihood of success on the merits, or by filing to intimidate, delay, or impose costs rather than to vindicate legitimate legal rights.

(f) **Anti-Patent Troll**: Any entity asserting patent claims against this work, its derivatives, or the author's use thereof, owes: the author's actual costs of defense plus a per-claim multiplier of 5× the claimed damages for each claim not prevailed on. Filing a patent challenge simultaneously with other legal or regulatory pressure constitutes bad faith and triggers the multiplier.

(g) **Anti-Trademark Squatting**: No entity may register trademarks on the names "Time License," "TimeLord," "Temporal Telepathy," "chem-es," or substantially similar identifiers in any jurisdiction for any purpose related to the subject matter of this work or the author's published work.

(h) **Anti-Laches and Anti-Estoppel**: Delay by the author in asserting rights under this license does not constitute waiver, estoppel, or laches. The author's rights are preserved regardless of the time elapsed between a violation and enforcement.

(i) **Anti-Inversion and Priority Challenge**: No entity may challenge the author's priority of invention, discovery, or publication for content in this work by asserting that equivalent results were produced earlier without contemporaneous public disclosure. Unpublished internal research does not defeat the author's published prior art.

(j) **Severability**: If any provision of this license is unenforceable in any jurisdiction, the remainder continues in full force. The Human Rights Bar (Section 5) is not severable — if Section 5 is unenforceable as a whole in any jurisdiction, this license does not apply in that jurisdiction and all rights revert to the author.

